                <head>Speech of Hon. Edward Everett</head>
                <origin/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <commentary>"At the great Union meeting in Boston on the 8th inst., the Hon. Edward
                    Everett delivered the following speech:"</commentary>
                <names/>
                <summary>Speech of Everett on the importance of Union and the need for both
                    moderation and compromise in both North and South. Very long (3+ cols.), touches
                    on Harper's Ferry and African slave trade.</summary>
            </div>
