        <page n="03" image="va.au.ss.1859.12.20.03">
            <div type="l">
                <column>1</column>
                <head>Correspondence of Spectator; New York, Dec. 14, 1859</head>
                <origin/>
                <excerpt>"[The New York Herald] is like Beecher's sermons, of which somebody has
                    said that if they had any religion in them they would be spoiled."</excerpt>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer>Yours truly, VA.</trailer>
                <commentary/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Letter from travelling correspondent regarding the political climate in New
                    York. Indicts New York Herald and Tribune for trying to play North against
                    South.</summary>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>2</column>
                <head/>
                <origin/>
                <excerpt>"Wm. H. Seward has effectively cut his own jugular, and is as politically
                    dead as Aaron Burr and Benedict Arnold."</excerpt>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <commentary/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Criticizes Seward for praising Helper's Impending Crisis.</summary>
            </div>
